article.headline: Wofford 70, Bradley 66
article.story: PEORIA, Ill. -- Kevin Giltner scored 29 points Tuesday night to lead Wofford to a 70-66 victory over Bradley. Giltner was 11 for 17 from the field, including 5 for 8 from behind the 3-point line for the Terriers (2-2). Drew Crowell had 12 points and 10 rebounds and Karl Cochran added 12 points and eight rebounds for Wofford. Brad Loesing had nine points and eight assists for Wofford. Dyricus Simms-Edwards led Bradley (3-1) with 22 points. Taylor Brown had 16 points and 11 rebounds for Bradley and Walt Lemon Jr. scored 14 points. Wofford was 10 for 23 (44 percent) from 3-point range while Bradley was just 4 for 17, or 24 percent, from the longer distance.
